{
  "doc_id": "37266",
  "text": "Although ANM depend on the number of available experimental structures in order to obtain meaningful results, MD simulations are subject to the sampling problem of the conformational space. [CITATION_1] We tried to address the MD sampling limitations by using accelerated molecular dynamics (aMD), which provide access to events beyond those obtained with conventional MD (described in Accelerated MD of the rCUG system model). Finally, we discuss the conformational space obtained by all these methods and compare them to those conformers obtained by deformation of the ANM softest normal modes (Comparison of ANM, PCA and EDA modes).",
